> >It defines following constructs:
> >
> >* module ModuleName in [Namespace|Namespace.Namespace]
>=20
> This method of defining namespaces would require some form=20
> of central authority allocating namespace "domains" to=20
> developers, so as to acertain that no two companies or users=20
> will use the same namespace for their projects. Since this=20
> would put unnecessary burden on INRIA and on the developers,=20
> I advocate, as I already mentioned, the XML solution: a=20
> namespace is an arbitrary string literal enclosed by double=20
> quotes. The convention would be for each company or=20
> developer to use URLs pertaining to domains officially=20
> belonging to them.
>=20

